  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "If you're receiving Likes from people in India on an ad campaign targeted specifically to San Francisco, several potential reasons could explain this discrepancy:\n\n1. **VPN Usage**: Some users in India may be using VPN services to change their IP addresses, making it appear as if they are located in San Francisco.\n\n2. **Proxies or Misconfigured Devices**: Occasionally, people might use proxies or have misconfigured device settings that inaccurately report their location.\n\n3. **Ad Platform Error**: There might be an error or bug in the ad platform's targeting system that's causing your ad to be served outside your specified location.\n\n4. **Interest and Behavior Targeting**: If you've included interests or behavioral targeting in addition to geographic targeting, users outside San Francisco who are aligned with those interests might still see your ad.\n\n5. **Ad Reshares**: Someone in San Francisco could have engaged with your ad and then reshared it, leading to additional visibility beyond your target area.\n\n6. **Default Data**: In some cases, inaccuracies in how location data is handled on ad platforms might lead to ads being distributed outside the selected location.\n\n7. **Manual Data Entry Errors**: In platforms where users fill in their location manually, entries might not always be accurate or up-to-date.\n\nTo address this issue, you can double-check your ad settings to ensure everything is configured correctly. If the problem persists, reaching out to the customer support team of the ad platform with specific details might help clarify the situation and explore if there's a technical issue at play.",
